---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const SITE = 'https://www.indiespeedrun.com';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: SITE + '/' },
  { name: 'Methodology', url: SITE + '/methodology/' },
];
---

<Base
  title="Methodology — How IndieSpeedRun Curates & Verifies"
  description="How IndieSpeedRun selects indie games, verifies speedrun records, and applies editorial standards. Explicit criteria, traceable sources, no fabricated claims."
  canonicalPath="/methodology/"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8 flex gap-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-gray-300">Home</a>
      <span>/</span>
      <span class="text-gray-300">Methodology</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Methodology</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-10">How we select, verify, and update our coverage</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-300">
      <p class="text-xl">
        Every recommendation and data table on this site follows explicit, repeatable criteria. This page documents those criteria so readers can evaluate our picks and flag errors.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Speedrun World Records</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-6 mb-2">Source</h3>
      <p>
        All world-record data is sourced from <a href="https://www.speedrun.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">speedrun.com</a>, the community-verified leaderboard. Each record table links directly to its leaderboard. We do not report records from other sources unless noted.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-6 mb-2">Freshness</h3>
      <p>
        Record pages carry a visible "last verified" date. We check and update records weekly. If a record changes and the page hasn't been updated within 10 days, treat the data as provisional.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-6 mb-2">Category selection</h3>
      <p>
        We cover the categories most searched and discussed in the community — typically Any%, Glitchless, and major category extensions. We don't fabricate minor categories to pad a table. If a category is niche enough that most readers won't recognise it, we explain it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Indie Game Picks</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-6 mb-2">Criteria applied to every pick</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-3 list-none">
        {[
          ['Critical reception', 'Minimum 75 on OpenCritic or equivalent scene consensus. No games selected solely on our own unverified opinion.'],
          ['Originality', 'Genuine design novelty — not just "indie" in the business sense. Games published by major publishers under indie-style packaging are flagged.'],
          ['Speedrun-friendliness', 'Our unique column. Scored 1–5: route diversity, skip / exploit potential, load-time fairness, active leaderboard on speedrun.com. This is the angle no competitor has.'],
          ['Availability', 'Must be purchasable or free at time of publication. Abandonware included only when it\'s the canonical entry for a historic category.'],
        ].map(([label, desc]) => (
          <li class="border border-gray-800 rounded p-4">
            <span class="font-semibold text-gray-100">{label}: </span>
            <span>{desc}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-100 mt-6 mb-2">What we don't claim</h3>
      <p>
        We don't say "we played every game on this list." We say what we checked: critical scores, speedrun.com leaderboard activity, developer documentation. When we recommend a game we've played, we say so. When we haven't, we don't pretend otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Corrections Policy</h2>
      <p>
        Factual errors (wrong WR holder, wrong time, wrong release year) are corrected within 48 hours when reported. Open a GitHub issue with a source link. Opinion disagreements are noted but don't trigger corrections.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Affiliates & Monetisation</h2>
      <p>
        Any affiliate link (e.g. Steam referral) is labelled. We don't rank games higher because of affiliate relationships — the criteria above apply regardless. At launch this site carries no affiliate links; that will be disclosed here if it changes.
      </p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-8 mt-10 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <p>Last updated: June 2026. This page is versioned in the site's GitHub repo.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
